## Stance output (STRICT JSON — malformed lines are discarded)

Emit ONE fenced block tagged `stances`, JSONL, exactly one stance per card, in exactly this
shape (`stance` is one of support|support_with_revision|reject):

```stances
{{SCHEMA_STANCES}}
```

- support — the evidence establishes the bug as stated.
- support_with_revision — the bug is real, but severity/location/category/claim needs adjustment;
  put the corrected value(s) in `revision` (omit fields you don't change).
- reject — the evidence does not establish the bug; your `rationale` is the counter-evidence.

`new_evidence` is optional (a single new located fact for THIS issue); omit it if none.

**Blindness — write only technical facts.** Every `new_evidence`, plus the `rationale` from a `reject`
or `support_with_revision` stance, is carried VERBATIM onto the cards the other reviewers read next
round. State only what the code does and why. NEVER
mention the other reviewers, how many reviewers there are, or whether anyone agrees or disagrees —
no "all three", "both", "the other reviewer", "we agree", "consensus", "unanimous", "majority", no
model/tool names (Codex, GPT, Gemini, Claude). A stance whose text references the panel or its tally
is rejected and re-requested, so keep every word about the code, not the review.

