```

A `new_findings` entry must be a **defect** (a bug/risk/weakness that warrants a change) — never a
confirmation that the code is correct or a restatement of intended behavior. **Always emit the
`new_findings` block**, even when you have nothing new: put an empty array `[]` inside it (or leave
it empty) if you are proposing no new issue. Do not invent a finding just to fill the block.

